no-process-exit.description:
Description

This rule aims to prevent the use ofprocess.exit()in Node.js JavaScript. As such, it warns wheneverprocess.exit()is found in code.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-process-exit: "error"*/

process.exit(1);
process.exit(0);

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-process-exit: "error"*/

Process.exit();
var exit = process.exit;
